	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Change use fists to use 1hb or h2h(martial) weapons until higher levels. Trust me, two polished steel ulaks are perfectly affordable by level 10, and your DPS will be far better with those. Then upgrade to a PSU in primary and cane of tranquil in offhand by level 20. A bear fanged glove is also a nice, low dly primary that you can get under 200p, but it doesn't have any stats... that's my advice anyway, keep a h2h and a 1hb and build 2hb if you want/can. Personally I've always just preferred to use dual weild because it looks cooler hehehehe :P<BR>
<BR>
Also, don't make the mistake of using fireclaw talons. Don't get me wrong, they're awesome on a BST with high dex, who can keep them proccing often enough to offset the crappy ratio, but as a monk, 28/6 is just way too high of a delay and too low of a damage to make them worthwhile.<BR>
<BR>
Change learn to fish to learn to bake - stat foods are a monk's best friend. Just grab yourself some obaha(SP?) truffles and grobb liquidized meat for a quick STR/STA/AGI/DEX boost that's also fairly cheap.<BR>
<BR>
Also, to the dude that posted below... I do believe you're incorrect on the AC. Agility affects your ability to use skills such as dodge successfully. AC affects how *hard* the opponent will hit you, IE how much damage they do, not whether or not they make contact. Overall, just don't flame people who are trying to help or call them stupid or any of that crap, then everybody will be happier. Good luck with your monkies :P<BR>
<BR>
Sister Fexa Furyfists<BR>
65 Transcendent<BR>
Quellious
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
