	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Having played only casters prior to starting a monk, I found playing a monk unique.  First, I found that having equipment that is at or below 20 lbs does not seriously affect skills (e.g. attack, dodge, etc.) and the rate of skill increase seems to be the same.  Secondly, carrying a 1h weapon does not hinder development of h2h, and offers the benefit of having proficiency with at least 1h weapons. Thirdly, practicing any type of kick is crucial.  Fourthly, practice safe fall as often as possible. I have escaped many a mob by adding valuable seconds in a jumping from absurd heights. Finally, kindness has many rewards. Offer to back-up others in a fight if it looks like they are struggling. Very often they will offer to help you as well, and I have actually gotten paid a few times.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
